#. <section class="sutta" id="sn10.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn10.2:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn10.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Indakavagga"
msgstr "1. With Indaka"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 2. Sakkanāmasutta → sakkasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "sn10.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Sakkanāmasutta"
msgstr "2. With a Spirit Named Sakka"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.2:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak "
"Mountain."

# BB doesn’t comment on the name. A variant in the title says just Sakka, and he is addressed as Sakka by the Buddha. Perhaps he is called “named sakka” to differentiate him from THE Sakka.
msgctxt "sn10.2:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sakkanāmako yakkho yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then a spirit named Sakka went up to the Buddha, and addressed him in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. <a class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc805"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.2:2.1"
msgid "“Sabbaganthappahīnassa,"
msgstr "“You’ve given up all ties,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.2:2.2"
msgid "vippamuttassa te sato;"
msgstr "and are fully freed."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.2:2.3"
msgid "Samaṇassa na taṃ sādhu,"
msgstr "It’s not a good idea for you, ascetic,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: yadaññamanusāsasī”ti → yadaññamanusāsatīti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn10.2:2.4"
msgid "yadaññamanusāsasī”ti."
msgstr "to be instructing others.”"

# https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/teaching-from-compassion-and-attachment/3619
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. <a class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc806"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.2:3.1"
msgid "“Yena kenaci vaṇṇena,"
msgstr "“No matter what the apparent reason"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.2:3.2"
msgid "saṃvāso sakka jāyati;"
msgstr "why people are together, Sakka,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.2:3.3"
msgid "Na taṃ arahati sappañño,"
msgstr "it’s unworthy for a wise person"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.2:3.4"
msgid "manasā anukampituṃ."
msgstr "to not think of the other with compassion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.445"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. <a class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc807"></a>
msgctxt "sn10.2:4.1"
msgid "Manasā ce pasannena,"
msgstr "If you instruct others"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.2:4.2"
msgid "yadaññamanusāsati;"
msgstr "with a mind clear and confident,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn10.2:4.3"
msgid "Na tena hoti saṃyutto,"
msgstr "your compassion and empathy"

#. <br>
#. VAR: yānukampā → sānukampā (bj, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn10.2:4.4"
msgid "yānukampā anuddayā”ti."
msgstr "don’t create attachments.”"
